# Yale SOM Course Planner — agent context

Before coding, read in order:

1. `AGENTS.md`
2. `docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md`
3. `docs/PRD.md` (at least §6, §7, §11, §12)

## Workflow

- **One milestone or task = start a new Cursor agent** (new chat). Do not drag unrelated work across long threads.
- Work one PRD milestone at a time; stop after each for user approval (`approve` before continuing).
- Course data: only `docs/data-samples/courses_master_new.csv` (`days_clean`, `start_24h`, `end_24h`).
- Use `hasMeetingTime()` for calendar/conflict logic; untimed courses stay in the list but not on the calendar.

Do not commit unless the user asks. Never commit `.env`.
